---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy" description="Privacy policy for the Bloktastic website.">
  <section class="container-shell py-12">
    <article class="glass-card prose prose-slate max-w-3xl mx-auto p-6 lg:p-10">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>

      <p>Last updated: February 2026</p>

      <h2>Overview</h2>

      <p>
        Bloktastic is an open-source project maintained by Benedikt Grimm. This policy explains how the
        Bloktastic website handles visitor data.
      </p>

      <h2>What we collect</h2>

      <p>
        This website does not use cookies, tracking scripts, or analytics services. We do not collect
        personal data through this website.
      </p>

      <h2>Hosting</h2>

      <p>
        This website is hosted on <a href="https://vercel.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Vercel Inc.</a>,
        440 N Barranca Ave #4133, Covina, CA 91723, USA. When you visit this website, Vercel may process
        your IP address, browser type, operating system, referrer URL, and timestamp in server logs.
        This data processing is necessary to deliver the website (Art. 6(1)(f) GDPR â€” legitimate interest).
      </p>

      <p>
        Vercel may transfer data to the United States. Vercel participates in the EU-U.S. Data Privacy
        Framework and processes data in accordance with its
        <a href="https://vercel.com/legal/privacy-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">privacy policy</a>.
        We have no influence over the scope and duration of Vercel's data processing.
      </p>

      <h2>CLI tool</h2>

      <p>
        The Bloktastic CLI communicates with the Storyblok API using credentials you provide.
        The CLI does not send telemetry or usage data to Bloktastic. Your Storyblok tokens are
        stored locally and never transmitted to our servers.
      </p>

      <h2>GitHub</h2>

      <p>
        Our source code and registry are hosted on GitHub. When you interact with the
        <a href="https://github.com/bartundmett/bloktastic">GitHub repository</a> (issues, pull requests, discussions),
        GitHub's <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-general-privacy-statement" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">privacy policy</a> applies.
      </p>

      <h2>npm</h2>

      <p>
        The CLI package is distributed via npm. When you install it, npm's
        <a href="https://docs.npmjs.com/policies/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">privacy policy</a> applies.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes</h2>

      <p>
        We may update this policy from time to time. Changes will be reflected on this page with an
        updated date.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>

      <p>
        For privacy-related questions, open an issue on
        <a href="https://github.com/bartundmett/bloktastic/issues">GitHub</a>.
      </p>
    </article>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style is:global>
  .prose h1 {
    margin-bottom: 1.2rem;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4.5vw, 2.8rem);
    font-weight: 800;
    color: #1b243f;
    line-height: 1.1;
  }

  .prose h2 {
    margin-top: 2.4rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    font-size: clamp(1.35rem, 3vw, 1.75rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    color: #1b243f;
  }

  .prose p,
  .prose li {
    color: #475569;
    line-height: 1.75;
  }

  .prose a {
    color: #0891b2;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
</style>
